Requirements: 
1. Build an MVC Sinatra Application
2. Use ActiveRecord
3. Use at least one has_many relationship on a User model and one belongs_to relationship on another model
4. Have user signup and login functionality using bcrypt to secure passwords
5. Validate uniqueness of user login attribute (username or email)
6. Be able to see all resources that belong to other users
7. Have full CRUD capabilities on the resource that belongs to that user
8. Do NOT have the ability to edit or delete a resource that belongs to other users
9. Validate user input so that bad data cannot be persisted to the database


beauty store app:
- user can view order form R
- user can submit order C
- user can edit order U 
- user can delete order D

User class
- attr: name, password
- can sign up
- can log in
- has many orders

Orders class
- attr: item, item_price, total ?
- belongs to user 



